result.name: Diamond Café

reviews.text:
Pretty nice place. Locals are so nice. Food is grttt. Despite its outlooks, very clean food. 

The price? Very low. Would go there everyday, if I lived there.

Down to earth Hong Kong Restaurant, and tea shop. Locals hang out, talk chat and its lively and busy.   Prices are very reasonable.  Service fast, and friendly. In the mornings before 9:30 you can even sit outside on a table and chair (smokers area) or your own little area.   Quintessentially "local"

Unless you are locals, you probably visit this shop for the experience and not for the food (food tastes ok but nothing special). It is a time-weathered Hong Kong style cafe hidden in a quiet corner of a desolated market of an aged public housing estate. Acrylic table tops and decos have been discoloured by decades of wears and tears but the shop is not dirty in general. Items are very inexpensive and the portion is big. Service is fast and friendly. Photographers may be disappointed by its less photogenic decos.
Just okay

沒有任何蔬菜及配菜 
肉和壹pat汁 飯
全碟
枝竹豆腐斑腩飯，竟然係你永遠找不到 豆腐， 只有數嚿開邊的豆卜。
係呀！
我冇講錯，你冇聽錯， 竟然係豆卜， 我咁大個仔現在先知，豆腐同豆卜，原來係完全係同一樣嘢嚟嘅.....
豆腐即係豆卜，豆卜即係豆腐，好深奧嘅哲學
我呢一刻
望住啲碟飯，我算唔算中伏呢？

 而班腩就只會有得三嚿，細細斑腩， 諗諗下，老細你就發啦 
賣一箱，咪可以創業板上市，收費又算唔算合理呢？
p.s 飯底有一陣芳香清潔劑味 $42連凍飲。完！
